{
  "texts": [
    "Table 4: Instruction-tuned RETRO evaluation results.",
    "This study explores Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT) methods applied to Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) models, comparing GPT and RETRO architectures.",
    "RETRO generally outperforms GPT in zero-shot settings due to their pre-training process that integrates external retrieval, enhancing contextual understanding.",
    "However, GPT models show a higher performance potential with PEFT, indicating more room for improvement during fine-tuning.",
    "Both RETRO and GPT models perform optimally around the 8B parameter mark, balancing cost and performance."
  ]
}